ong-range order at zero fields is assigned to the effect\nof strong bond-frustration, arising from the complex spin-orbit entangled $4f$\nground state. Finally, we derive the highly anisotropic magnetic phase diagram,\nwhich is discussed in comparison with the existing theoretical models for\nspin-$\\frac{1}{2}$ triangular-lattice antiferromagnets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Nov 2019 13:45:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-29"}
